
San Roque Club
instance
The San Roque Club is a country club located in San Roque, in the Andalusia region in Southern Spain, a few miles from Gibraltar. The Old course was designed by Dave Thomas and constructed in 1990. The New course was added in 2002, and was designed by Perry Dye. The club hosted the Open de Espa?a in 2005 and 2006, and also hosts the Asprey Cup horse race. The chairman of the golf club was Seve Ballesteros.